This paper deals with optimization techniques for SPARQL queries on RDF graphs, which are typically stored in databases. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely category. The paper also proposes novel optimization strategies that involve nullification and best-match operators, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of compressed indexes, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and graph algorithms (cs.LG).
